143	// scan(pathsOrDirs) -> {violations, bundlesSeen, unreachableSeen}. Each entry may be a bundle
144	// file or a directory of *.json files (gate-cli supplies [CALIBRATE_DIR] under --calibrate).
145	//
146	// CR-41 (fail closed): a scan that never actually looked at anything must never report a clean
147	// "0 violation(s)" pass. Every one of the following is now folded into `violations` (as a
148	// facts-abstain/scan-error finding, the SAME channel a real non-abstain-emission finding uses, so
149	// runGateCli's exit code and --json output both pick it up with no second door to forget):
150	//   - zero paths/dirs supplied at all (a bare `node tools/facts-abstain/check.js` with no args)
151	//   - a supplied path that does not exist
